\section*{Professional Summary}

Engineer with 12+ years across full-stack product development, web3 infrastructure, high-performance computing, and ML research. I've shipped production systems at every layer—microservices and fintech platforms, CosmWasm smart contracts and on-chain architectures, real-time trading systems running on live capital—and I build research software independently, from neural operator pre-training frameworks to multilingual VAE decoders for emergent agent communication.

My earlier work in HPC (non-blocking data structures, parallel algorithms) and scientific computing still shapes how I think about systems at any level of the stack. Current interests center on quantitative trading and systematic strategy development, and on AI research in pre-training methods and scientific machine learning—neural operators, emergent communication, and foundation models for physical systems.

I came to computer science through comparative religion and a curiosity about complex systems, not through a traditional engineering track. That path has had a lasting influence on how I approach design problems—I tend to reach for ideas across disciplines and pick up new domains quickly.

