\section*{Selected Technical Projects}

\subsection*{LFM — Language Faculty Model}
\textbf{GitHub:} \href{https://github.com/dgabriele/lfm}{github.com/dgabriele/lfm} | PyTorch, VAE, REINFORCE, SentencePiece

Agents embedded in complex systems develop internal representations that encode perspectives no human has access to—but have no way to express them. LFM gives those agents a language. A multilingual VAE decoder pretrained on 560K IPA-transcribed sentences from 16 typologically diverse languages is frozen as a linguistic bottleneck, analogous to a Chomskyan Universal Grammar: agents learn only to project representations into the decoder's latent space, and the fixed structural prior constrains output to be phonotactically well-formed, compositional, and variable-length—avoiding the known failure modes of emergent communication (degenerate codes, anti-Zipfian distributions, non-compositional collapse). The emergent language is alien but structurally natural, making it translatable by a fine-tuned LLM the same way it would learn any unfamiliar natural language. Achieves 95\% accuracy (15.2x above chance) on 16-way referential games with hard semantic negatives. Latent space recovers typological groupings across language families, exhibits Zipfian token statistics, Lipschitz smoothness (r=0.86), and adaptive length scaling (r=0.947). Includes 11-command CLI visualization suite for publication-quality structural diagnostics.

\subsection*{Spinlock — Neural Operator Pre-Training Framework}
\textbf{GitHub:} \href{https://github.com/dgabriele/spinlock}{github.com/dgabriele/spinlock} | PyTorch, U-AFNO, Neural Operators, VQ-VAE

Pre-training framework for neural operators over continuous dynamical systems (e.g.\ Lenia continuous cellular automata, reaction-diffusion PDEs). Generates large-scale trajectory datasets via Sobol-stratified parameter sampling, extracts multi-modal behavioral features, and trains U-AFNO meta-operators as fast surrogate world models across diverse dynamics. Includes two tokenization pathways: a VQ-VAE discrete codebook for behavioral clustering, and an NLTokenizer that integrates with LFM's frozen linguistic decoder—encoding trajectory dynamics into a continuous VAE latent space, projecting through Gumbel-Softmax into LFM's frozen autoregressive decoder, and verifying fidelity via a listener roundtrip loss. The goal: agents that observe dynamical systems and describe what they see in their own emergent language, translatable to English via a fine-tuned LLM.

\subsection*{Nature — Genetic Programming Framework}
\textbf{GitHub:} \href{https://github.com/dgabriele/nature}{github.com/dgabriele/nature} | Python, Grammar Evolution

Open source framework that evolves Python instance methods via \texttt{@evolve} decorator. Multi-objective optimization over arbitrary datatypes (Pandas, NumPy, CuPy) outperforming DEAP. Built for generating adaptive trading rule ensembles.

\subsection*{Reactor — Procedural Generative Art Framework}
\textbf{GitHub:} \href{https://github.com/superginyuforce/reactor}{github.com/superginyuforce/reactor} | Node.js, TypeScript, Canvas API

Framework for procedural art generation with unified brush abstraction supporting parametric control over geometric primitives. Implements lazy evaluation proxy pattern for stroke dynamics with deterministic PRNG for reproducible variation. Produces high-resolution outputs (15000×15000px) for physical mockups and print-on-demand.

\subsection*{PampIt — Token Launchpad}
\textbf{GitHub:} \href{https://github.com/Gelotto/pampit}{github.com/Gelotto/pampit} | \textbf{Live:} \href{https://pampit.fun}{pampit.fun} | Next.js, Rust, CosmWasm

Production token launchpad across 6 Cosmos chains with zero backend infrastructure. Custom RPC batching client reducing distributed query latency 10x (4000ms $\rightarrow$ 400ms). Responsive UX with client-side pub/sub polling and pagination. All business logic in Rust smart contracts.

